# CONNECTIONS
OAuth connections to external services. Two ways to make authenticated API calls:

**Option 1: Direct API call** (recommended for simple requests)
Use `distri_request` to proxy through the connection — auth token is injected automatically:
```
distri_request({
  path: "/connections/<connection_id>/request",
  method: "POST",
  body: {
    method: "GET",
    url: "https://api.example.com/endpoint",
    headers: {},
    body: null
  }
})
```

**Option 2: Code execution** (for scripts, data processing, chaining calls)
Inject the token as an env var, then use `call_coder`:
```
inject_connection_env({ connection_id: "<id>" })
// Then in call_coder: token = os.getenv("<PROVIDER>_TOKEN")
```

**NEVER pass raw tokens in conversation messages.**
If scopes are insufficient, reconnect with additional scopes via the connections API.

